text: Jean-Yves Le Déaut (born February 1, 1945 in Guémené-sur-Scorff) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Meurthe-et-Moselle department, and is a member of the Socialiste, radical, citoyen et divers gauche. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:Living people Category:People from Guémené-sur-Scorff Category:Socialist Party (France) politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
title: Jean-Yves Le Déaut
